From David Mckissock Subject Blue Ribbon Panel Members Named The following press release was distributed April by NASA Space Station Redesign Advisory Members Named Along with Charles Vest recently named by Vice President Albert Gore to head the advisory committee on the redesign of the Space Station NASA has announced the names of representatives from government and industry and academic experts from across the country to participate in an independent review of the redesign options being developed by I am extremely honored to have been selected to lead this important review America's future in science and technology and as a world leader in space demands our utmost attention and care said We have assembled a diverse panel of experts that I believe will bring the appropriate measures of insight integrity and objectivity to this critical The advisory committee is charged with independently assessing various redesign options of the space station presented by NASA's redesign team and proposing recommendations to improve efficiency and effectiveness of the space station Space station international partners also are being asked to participate and will be named at a later The advisory committee will submit its recommendations in Advisory committee members named today include Charles Vest Bobby Alford President MIT Executive VP Dean of Medicine Baylor College of Medicine Jay Chabrow Paul Chu President JMR Associates Director Texas Center for Superconductivity University of Houston Ed Crawley John Fabian Prof of Aero Astro President CEO MIT ANSER James Fain Edward Fort Deputy Chief of Staff for Chancellor Requirements Headquarters North Carolina AT T USAF Materials Command State University Mary Good Frederick Hauck Senior VP of Technology President International Technical Allied Signal Underwriters Lou Lanzerotti William Lilly Chair Space Sciences National Academy of Public Board National Research Administration Council Duane McRuer Brad Parkinson President Systems Technology Prof of Astro Aero Stanford University Robert Seamans Lee Silver Former NASA Deputy Keck Foundation Professor for Resource Geology California Institute of Technology Albert Bud Wheelon Retired CEO Hughes Aircraft